The main thread in a Console application is special. Since it is the only foreground thread, when it exits, the entire application exits.

If you are using C# 7.1 or newer, you can specify an `async Task Main` method as such:

```C#
static async Task Main()
{
  await Work();
}
```

Under the hood, this will block your main thread until the operation completes. For older versions of C#, you can do this yourself:

```C#
static void Main()
{
  Work().GetAwaiter().GetResult();
}
```

Normally, [you do *not* want to block on asynchronous code][1]; the `Main` method of a Console application is an *exception* to this rule.


  [1]: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/jj991977.aspx

